q=75;w=3840&amp;q=75 2x" alt="Bar Design NYC, Bolt, Bolt Builds, Bolt Builds NYC, Bolt Builds New York City, Bolt Design NYC, Bolt New York City, Boutique Design Agency New York, Custom Interior Design New York, Custom millwork NYC, Elegant Hospitality Interiors NYC, High-End Bar Design NYC, High-End Interior Design Agency NYC, High-End Retail Design New York, High-end Millwork NYC, Hospitality, Hospitality Interior Design New York, Innovative Hospitality Solutions New York, Luxery Millwork NYC, Luxury Bar Design NYC, Luxury Hospitality Consultants NYC, Luxury Millwork NYC, NYC Residential Interior Designers, New York, New York City, New York Design and Branding for Hospitality, New York Hospitality Branding, New York Retail Interior Design, Sophisticated Branding Agency NYC, luxury Hospitality Design NYC" width="1447" height="859" class="absolute object-cover w-full h-full z-0 inset-0" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 300vw, (max-width: 1000px) 200vw, 100vw"/></div><div class="border-x flex-1 flex flex-col justify-end"></div></header><div class="z-20 relative bg-white"><div class="sticky top-0 invisible"><div class="px-unit absolute left-0 right-0 bg-white"><div class="pt-unit border-black border-b"></div></div></div><div class="px-unit"><div class="pt-unit border-black border-x"><div class="sticky top-unit"><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit pt-2 pb-4"><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-3 pr-2"><p class="text-current font-body text-3xl">Junior Designer</p></div><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-2"><h3 class="text-current font-body text-md">February 4, 2026</h3></div></div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit pt-8 pb-unit"><div class="col-start-1 col-end-13 md:col-start-2 md:col-end-12 lg:col-start-4 lg:col-end-12 xl:col-start-4 xl:col-end-10"><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>About Bolt</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Bolt is a full-service <strong>Design + Build</strong> firm and fully insured <strong>General Contractor</strong> based in Brooklyn. We specialize in design-forward hospitality, retail, and residential projects that merge classical sensibility with innovative construction and fabrication methods. We believe that great design is only as strong as its execution — and that means being just as rigorous about budgets, schedules, and communication as we are about creative vision.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>The Role</strong></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Bolt Builds is seeking a motivated and detail-oriented <strong>Interior Design Intern</strong> to support our design and construction team across hospitality, retail, and residential projects. This role is ideal for someone eager to gain hands-on experience in a fast-paced design-build studio, learn directly from senior designers, and see their work move quickly from concept to construction.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">As a Design Intern, you’ll participate actively in the studio, contribute creatively, and develop a strong foundation in design development, documentation, and professional studio practice.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Design Development Support</strong><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Assist with drafting, modeling, and rendering design concepts using <strong>Rhino, Revit, and Adobe Creative Suite</strong></li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Support the creation of presentation decks, mood boards, and visual narratives</li></ul></li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>FF&amp;E Research &amp; Documentation</strong><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Conduct product and materials research aligned with project budgets and creative direction</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Help maintain and organize FF&amp;E schedules and supporting documentation under senior designer guidance</li></ul></li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Project Documentation</strong><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Assist in maintaining drawing sets throughout design and construction phases</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Ensure files are organized according to Bolt’s documentation standards</li></ul></li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Studio Participation</strong><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Attend team meetings, client presentations, and site visits as needed</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Take clear notes and follow through on assigned action items</li></ul></li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Material Library &amp; Sample Management</strong><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Help organize and maintain physical samples and material library updates</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Request samples and follow up with vendors for active projects</li></ul></li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Professional Standards</strong><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Uphold Bolt’s core values of <strong>Accountability, Quality, Innovation, and Reliability</strong></li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Maintain a professional, proactive attitude with clients, vendors, and teammates</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Demonstrate strong communication, ownership, and eagerness to learn</li></ul></li></ul><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></p><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Currently pursuing or recently completed a degree in <strong>Interior Design, Architecture, or a related field</strong></li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Strong interest in <strong>design-build environments</strong> and seeing projects through from concept to construction</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Working knowledge of <strong>Rhino, Revit, and Adobe Creative Suite</strong> (or strong willingness to learn quickly)</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Strong organizational skills and attention to detail</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Ability to take direction, ask thoughtful questions, and follow through on tasks</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Clear and professional written and verbal communication skills</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Comfortable working in a fast-paced, collaborative studio environment</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Curious, proactive, and eager to learn — with a positive, can-do attitude</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4">Passion for hospitality, retail, and thoughtfully designed spaces</li></ul><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Why Bolt</strong></p><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>See your work built — and built fast.</strong> At Bolt, you won’t be stuck pushing paper for years before seeing results. Our projects move quickly, and the work you put in becomes something real, tangible, and lasting.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Be hands-on.</strong> You won’t be siloed behind a screen — you’ll be in the field, in meetings, on walk-throughs, and fully involved in the process from start to finish.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Work in the heart of Greenpoint.</strong> Our studio is based in one of Brooklyn’s most creative neighborhoods — surrounded by great food, inspiring spaces, and a thriving design community.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Join a company on the rise.</strong> Bolt is entering a new chapter of growth — and we’re building something special. You’ll help shape the future of the company, not just execute the present.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Build projects you’re proud of.</strong> From thoughtful restaurants to bold retail environments, you’ll be part of a team that sweats the details and cares deeply about design, craft, and execution.</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Work with good people.</strong> We’re a tight-knit, driven team that takes pride in what we do — and has fun doing it. We value trust, accountability, and creative problem-solving.</li></ul><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><strong>Compensation</strong></p><ul class="space-y-2"><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Hourly Rate:</strong> $20/hour, depending on experience and qualifications</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Location:</strong> In-person, Greenpoint, Brooklyn</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Schedule:</strong> Full-time</li><li class="list-disc list-outside ml-4"><strong>Growth:</strong> Performance-based bonuses and clear pathways for professional development</li></ul><div class="mt-16 pb-12"><div class="px-6 py-8 bg-faint text-center"><p class="text-current font-body text-xl">To apply for this job, please email your resume to<!-- --> <a href="mailto:hello@bolt.build" class="font-bold hover:text-blue transition-colors border-b border-current border-dotted">hello@bolt.build ↗</a>.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><footer class="bg-white pb-unit px-unit relative z-[1000]"><div class="bg-white border border-b border-black pt-unit pb-unit"><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit"><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-3"><a class="text-current hover:text-yellow transition-colors" href="../index.html"><div class="w-[24px]"><div class="w-full "><svg width="100%" he